The bail application of a suspect alleged to be a Facebook serial rapist has been postponed at Qumbu Magistrate’s Court. Xolisa Sijada briefly appeared before the court on Tuesday as his bail application was postponed to, November 13, for a formal bail application. The 28-year-old Sijada is alleged to have invited women on Facebook posting a fake profile and picture. He will then arrange to meet his victims in Qumbu sending them transport money via money market from two major retail outlets. Out of seven cases opened at SAPS Qumbu three were murder and four rape cases. Police Captain Khaya Tonjeni said the victims were from Alice, Duncan Village, Mthatha, Tabankulu and Mount Fletcher. Sijada was charged with four counts of rape, three counts of murder and three counts of robbery with aggravating circumstances. TNA Reporter  